The paper presents a novel approach to apply DCRNN for a large highway network, which involves graph partitioning and training smaller networks simultaneously on a cluster with GPUs. This approach is related to machine learning (ML) and neural networks (NN), which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the spatiotemporal dynamics of traffic, which is related to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves computational and memory bottlenecks, which are related to the sub-category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.AI, and cs.DC, in that order.
